  "notes": "Element-wise arctan(y/x) considering quadrant.",
  "notes_sections": [
    "*arctan2* is identical to the `atan2` function of the underlying C library.  The following special values are defined in the C standard: [1]_",
    "====== ====== ================ `x1`   `x2`   `arctan2(x1,x2)` ====== ====== ================ +/- 0  +0     +/- 0 +/- 0  -0     +/- pi > 0   +/-inf +0 / +pi < 0   +/-inf -0 / -pi +/-inf +inf   +/- (pi/4) +/-inf -inf   +/- (3*pi/4) ====== ====== ================",
    "Note that +0 and -0 are distinct floating point numbers, as are +inf and -inf."
  ],
